  <h4 class="font-semibold">TL;DR</h4>
  <p>
    This ERC defines a standard interface for commit-reveal schemes. It provides a generic <code>commit</code> function that can be added to any contract, allowing users to commit to an action without revealing it immediately. This helps prevent front-running attacks and adds a layer of privacy to applications like voting systems. The reveal mechanism is intentionally left open for developers to implement as needed.
  </p>

  <h4 class="font-semibold">Specification</h4>
  <p>
    The standard defines two interfaces for implementing commit-reveal schemes. The core interface is minimal for backward compatibility, while the general interface provides more features.
  </p>
  <pre class="language-solidity"><code>{`interface IERC_COMMIT_CORE {
    function commit(bytes32 _commitment) payable external;
}

interface IERC_COMMIT_GENERAL {
    event Commit(
        uint256 indexed _timePoint,
        address indexed _from,
        bytes32 indexed _commitment,
        bytes _extraData);

    function commitFrom(
        address _from,
        bytes32 _commitment,
        bytes calldata _extraData)
    payable external returns(uint256 timePoint);
}`}
</code></pre>
